  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Alliance for Children Everywhere (ACE) rescues children who otherwise have little chance of survival, caring for them in temporary crisis homes. ACE also provides milk, medicine and other basic necessities to families and facilitates adoptions. ACE works with the Zambian people, respecting their insight about how they can be helped to care for their children and rebuild their nation. In addition, ACE helps churches provide free primary and middle school education and nutritious daily lunches for more than 2,500 children each year so they can grow up to lead families, communities, and their country.  http://childreneverywhere.org/</narrative>
  </description>
